##Separate folder just for modelling files. I'll try to time-tag them to keep track! 



iid_sampling_model is a model sampling trials and models iid, meaning no higher level structure guides the decision, but it is always just randomly selected. 
Models here seem to work just fine. 
In this code, some plotting happens as well. 6 plots come out; 3 for the loss function and 3 for the accuracy, 1 for each model. 

I also uploaded another file iid_nested_vs_alone for comparing how the models do when they are trained by themselves vs when they are trained with output of previous models. 
Models still seem to indicate a benefit for using earlier information. 

For any questions, please contact me. 
